Detailed Description

The main window in the MapEditor.

Has a map-area and the main manu.

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

MEMapEditorWindow::MEMapEditorWindow (  OldGenericMap *  map,
MC2String  gdfRefDir
) 
 

Create a new MEMapEditorWindow for a given map.

This window contains a map-area (that is created in this constructor) to the left and a menu to the right.

Parameters:
map The map that will be shown in the MEMapArea.
gdfRefFile Explicit directory of gdf ref file to load. Otherwise first found gdf ref is loaded.

bool MEMapEditorWindow::getMc2Coordinates (  char *  latString,
char *  lonString,
int32 &  mc2lat,
int32 &  mc2lon
)  [private]
 

Method that takes the coordinate strings and converts them to mc2 coordinates.

Used for searchCoordinatePressed and zoomToCoordinatePressed, so they can take both mc2 and wgs84 degrees coordinates.

Returns:
True if the mc2 coordinate out params are set, false if not.

The text file was created e.g. with MapTool --compturns option to report turn descriptions that differ when comparing two otherwise identical mcm maps.
